{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17412826","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17412826"},"attributes":{"position":3,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261079"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261079"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11728"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17511240","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17511240"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:39:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:39:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11728"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261079","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261079"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:40:20+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T08:44:36+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":4,"questionsAnswered":3,"marksTotal":4,"marksAttainable":3,"marksAttempted":3,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T07:41:39+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"11728","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11728"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.08,0.32,0.36,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4341"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98663"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4341","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4341"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11728"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81057"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"518"},{"type":"tags","id":"1110"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5958"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8841"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8956"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33819"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36916"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/98663"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 40-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a two-day history of increasing colicky abdominal pain and distension. He has no significant medical history apart from a Roux-en-Y gastric bypass six months ago for obesity. He takes no regular medications. He reports increasing fatigue over the past month which he attributed to starting night shift work. He works as a security guard.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears uncomfortable. His pulse rate is 95/min, blood pressure 125/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. His BMI is 28 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. His abdomen is distended but soft with generalised mild tenderness. Bowel sounds are hyperactive. A CT scan is performed (Image 1, 2).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of his bowel obstruction?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Internal hernia","Appendix mass","Band adhesion","Carcinoma of the caecum","Small bowel intussusception"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe CT scan shows dilated bowel loops with a transition point at the caecum where there is a mass lesion (Image 1). \u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the caecum\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents insidiously with iron deficiency anaemia and fatigue rather than obstructive symptoms, due to the capacious nature of the right colon and liquid stool content. The patient\u0027s fatigue, which was attributed to shift work, may have been an early symptom of the underlying malignancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInternal hernia\u003C/strong\u003E is a recognised complication following Roux-en-Y gastric bypass and can cause bowel obstruction. However, the CT appearances would typically show clustered bowel loops through a mesenteric defect rather than a mass lesion at the caecum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eappendix mass \u003C/strong\u003E(Image 2) typically appears as an inflammatory phlegmon with surrounding fat stranding and would be accompanied by a history of right iliac fossa pain and systemic inflammatory response. These features are not present in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBand adhesion \u003C/strong\u003E(Image 3) causing bowel obstruction would show an abrupt transition point with a characteristic \u0027beak sign\u0027 on CT, without an associated mass lesion. While the patient has had previous surgery, the CT appearance is not consistent with adhesional obstruction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall bowel intussusception\u003C/strong\u003E (Image 4) has a characteristic \u0027target sign\u0027 appearance on CT and typically occurs proximal to the ileocaecal valve. The CT in this case shows a mass lesion at the caecum rather than the typical appearance of intussusception.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Carcinoma of the caecum commonly presents with iron deficiency anaemia and fatigue rather than typical colonic symptoms.","Right-sided colonic tumours can present late as the caecum is distensible and stool content is liquid.","CT imaging is essential in diagnosing the cause of bowel obstruction and identifying the transition point."],"references":["Armstrong CP, Ahsan Z, Hinchley G, Brodribb AJ. Carcinoma of the caecum. J R Coll Surg Edinb. 1990 Apr;35(2):88-92. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2355383/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81057"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11728"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19991"},{"type":"media","id":"19992"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20415"},{"type":"media","id":"21838"},{"type":"media","id":"21839"},{"type":"media","id":"21840"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19991","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19991"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/2439f11b-22c2-434c-b7df-3ae04b0e2ca4.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/2439f11b-22c2-434c-b7df-3ae04b0e2ca4.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":440,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"19992","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19992"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f0a733aa-d647-45f1-ba75-9ad42f6ace14.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f0a733aa-d647-45f1-ba75-9ad42f6ace14.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1489,"height":1500}},{"type":"media","id":"20415","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20415"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/3vNQ9nr8fhk8e8VyRs8V8ad9MTn2gg.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/3vNQ9nr8fhk8e8VyRs8V8ad9MTn2gg.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":440,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"21838","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21838"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"h